programme.title: Iowa
programme.desc: After Killing Evander, we felt really good about going back to Illinois and getting an opportunity at the buck we were after. The weather was right, it was late October, and it just seemed like everything was adding up for this to be a successful trip. Even though we saw the shooter we were after and another really good deer, after 4 days of hunting we decided to pack up again and try our luck in Iowa. For a hard core whitetail bow hunter chasing big deer its hard to beat sitting in a tree in Iowa at the end of October and early November. We couldn't have timed this up more perfect. The bucks were on their feet, we were seeing giant deer, and it was just a matter of time before we ran in to one in bow range. Sit back and enjoy the second episode of Whitetail Edge Season 4, "Iowa".

programme.title: Megladon

programme.title: 4th Times a Charm

A buck that scored over 200 inches. This year he heads down to North Carolina to chase an early season monster in velvet and the he is off to Illinois for some midwest rut action in November. Little did Chad know that this season would be the ultimate test of patience, perseverance, and hard luck. Join Chad on this weeks episode, "4th Times a Charm".

programme.title: Evander
programme.desc: Our trip to the midwest started in Illinois at a farm we have been hunting for a couple years now. The moon was perfect and the weather was cold but unfortunately the deer just were not moving. After 5 days of hunting in Illinois we decided to pack up and head to Kansas with our buddy Travis for a buck we nicknamed Evander. The hunting was a grind. We were hunting extremely hard, moving stands and checking the Spartan Cameras to try and better position ourselves but we just could not see that shooter buck we were looking for. We made a move to a cedar tree in a pinch point I really liked and on October 21st, we finally had an encounter with Evander. Although it was exciting to see him we were slightly heart broken that he never made it into bow range. The grind continued and finally 3 days later we had a full moon and decided to hunt that morning in the same cedar tree we saw Evander a few days prior. We were right in the middle of the action as soon as it got light out and well, the rest is history. Check out the full hunt on our first episode of Whitetail Edge Season 4 called, Evander.

programme.title: Baby

However, we feel it is equally as important to pass our hunting tradition along to the next generation and help get them involved. This week on Whitetail Edge join team member Corey Meinke as he shares this special hunt where he got his son Hunter involved. Hunter help put up trail cameras, make scrape trees, and put up tree stands. This is what hunting is all about and a hunt that Corey and his family will never forget.
